 The drama already started in the early hours of Monday between 02:00-03:00, when stones were thrown at vehicles on the N4 from the bridge at the Van Dyksdrift off-ramp. According to information www.mobserver.co.za received, havoc erupted this morning when a taxi drove over rocks that were packed on the N4 near the Van Dyksdrift off-ramp. Also read: Seven killed in multi-vehicle accident Due to damage underneath the vehicle, the taxi driver had to stop. At that moment, robbers, who most probably packed the rocks on the road, started shooting at the passengers in the taxi and robbed them of their belongings. One person had a wound on his foot and another a flesh wound on his knee. Also read: Body found floating in Klein Olifants